WEBVTT

00:02.870 --> 00:04.269
What do you know
about all of this?

00:04.338 --> 00:05.371
If I had all the answers,
I wouldn't need you,

00:05.473 --> 00:06.572
would I?
-Need me?

00:06.607 --> 00:07.940
Quinn: What the hell
did you expect?

00:08.042 --> 00:10.142
I expected to discover
the truth.

00:10.177 --> 00:13.245
I expected a partner
who would back me up!

00:13.280 --> 00:14.980
That's a negative.
We are done here.

00:15.049 --> 00:17.182
This is the breakthrough
we've been waiting for.

00:17.218 --> 00:18.384
[ Gunshot ]
Aah! [laughs]

00:18.452 --> 00:20.085
I'm glad
you feel that way --

00:20.121 --> 00:21.720
because there's something
I need you to do.

00:21.756 --> 00:23.589
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

00:23.624 --> 00:25.024
<i> I</i> can't keep
doing this.

00:25.092 --> 00:26.025
What are you saying?

00:26.060 --> 00:27.526
Project Blue Book.

00:27.561 --> 00:29.995
You need to make
a choice, now.

00:30.031 --> 00:31.030
[ Ominous chord strikes ]

00:31.098 --> 00:33.799
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

00:33.834 --> 00:43.208
♪

00:43.244 --> 00:52.951
♪

00:52.987 --> 01:02.694
♪

01:02.730 --> 01:12.438
♪

01:12.473 --> 01:22.181
♪

01:22.216 --> 01:31.924
♪

01:31.959 --> 01:41.633
♪

01:41.669 --> 01:51.376
♪

01:51.412 --> 01:55.347
♪

01:55.382 --> 01:58.650
[ Ring ]

01:58.752 --> 02:02.321
[ Ring ]

02:02.356 --> 02:06.125
[ Ring ]

02:06.227 --> 02:09.962
[ Ring ]

02:09.997 --> 02:13.098
[ Ring ]

02:13.200 --> 02:14.166
Project Blue Book.

02:14.201 --> 02:15.767
This is Dr. Allen Hynek.

02:15.803 --> 02:19.104
<i>You're still there.</i>

02:19.173 --> 02:20.606
I'm just trying
to get organized.

02:20.641 --> 02:23.075
♪

02:23.110 --> 02:24.643
You're having
second thoughts.

02:24.678 --> 02:29.481
♪

02:29.583 --> 02:30.549
<i> Allen?</i>

02:30.584 --> 02:31.717
Yes.

02:31.752 --> 02:33.285
No, I mean no.
I just --

02:34.522 --> 02:38.323
<i> I can't talk</i>
<i> right now, Mimi.</i>

02:38.359 --> 02:40.459
I keep feeling like --

02:40.494 --> 02:41.760
like we're
in danger.

02:41.795 --> 02:43.061
<i> We're fine.</i>
<i> I promise.</i>

02:43.097 --> 02:45.030
Just --

02:45.065 --> 02:45.964
I'll be home soon.

02:46.000 --> 02:47.866
♪

02:47.902 --> 02:48.834
Okay.

02:48.869 --> 02:50.836
♪

02:50.871 --> 02:51.970
<i> Bye.</i>

02:52.006 --> 02:52.905
Bye.

02:52.940 --> 03:02.481
♪

03:02.516 --> 03:12.224
♪

03:12.259 --> 03:14.326
♪

03:14.361 --> 03:16.295
I always thought she was
lovelier than the others.

03:16.330 --> 03:18.297
[ Car whooshes past ]

03:18.332 --> 03:19.198
[ Bird chirping ]

03:19.233 --> 03:20.666
Hmm.

03:20.701 --> 03:21.967
I can see why you
became so infatuated.

03:22.002 --> 03:23.435
You went through
my personal things.

03:23.470 --> 03:25.037
It was a revelation,
really.

03:25.072 --> 03:27.272
Do you know why?
'Cause you were right.

03:27.374 --> 03:29.942
She is the key.

03:29.977 --> 03:33.445
You're just not using
your...asset fully.

03:33.547 --> 03:35.581
What are you
suggesting?

03:35.616 --> 03:37.082
Let's say
Mrs. Hynek were

03:37.117 --> 03:38.884
to have a dalliance
of sorts

03:38.919 --> 03:41.453
and it was photographed.

03:41.488 --> 03:42.788
I'll bet her husband,

03:42.823 --> 03:45.324
the esteemed professor
and Air Force lackey,

03:45.359 --> 03:46.658
would do just
about anything

03:46.694 --> 03:49.094
to keep those photos
out of the public eye.

03:49.129 --> 03:51.563
Maybe even betray
his country.

03:51.599 --> 03:52.965
[ Seat squeaking ]

03:56.103 --> 03:57.236
I thought you
would've been excited

03:57.271 --> 04:00.372
about the idea.

04:00.474 --> 04:03.742
Oh, I see.

04:03.777 --> 04:05.010
You're worried
about betraying

04:05.045 --> 04:06.745
your "friendship"
with her.

04:06.780 --> 04:08.247
Oh.

04:08.282 --> 04:09.848
Is that gonna be
a problem, this time?

04:13.921 --> 04:15.721
I have given you

04:15.756 --> 04:18.557
enough chances

04:18.659 --> 04:21.493
and, if you don't do
as I wish,

04:21.562 --> 04:24.129
I will find my own
version of blackmail.

04:24.164 --> 04:32.137
♪

04:32.172 --> 04:33.071
Hit me.

04:33.107 --> 04:34.940
♪

04:35.042 --> 04:37.242
[whispering] Why?

04:37.311 --> 04:39.044
[whispering]
I said,

04:39.079 --> 04:40.812
hit. me.

04:40.848 --> 04:43.081
♪

04:43.150 --> 04:43.749
Why would I do that?

04:43.784 --> 04:46.618
♪

04:46.720 --> 04:47.686
Unh!

04:47.721 --> 04:49.554
What the fuck
was that?

04:49.657 --> 04:50.555
[ Scoff ]

04:50.591 --> 04:52.190
♪

04:52.226 --> 04:54.459
Using my asset fully
will not be a problem.

04:54.495 --> 04:55.794
♪

04:55.829 --> 04:57.229
I'll keep you posted.

04:57.264 --> 04:59.264
[ Groans ]

04:59.366 --> 05:00.966
Oh.
[ Door closes ]

05:01.001 --> 05:02.467
If they don't have
an appointment,

05:02.503 --> 05:03.869
I can't just --
Afternoon, Captain.

05:03.937 --> 05:06.271
-Any coffee on?
-Dr. Hynek is here.

05:09.610 --> 05:11.376
Yes.
Totally understood.

05:16.717 --> 05:17.849
You're here.

05:17.885 --> 05:20.652
Had to catch up
on some paperwork.

05:20.688 --> 05:22.287
Aren't you supposed
to be teaching a class?

05:22.323 --> 05:24.623
Well, I had some files
I wanted to go through first.

05:26.827 --> 05:28.760
All of them?

05:28.796 --> 05:33.799
[ Sigh ]

05:33.834 --> 05:36.802
What the hell
is this?

05:36.870 --> 05:38.503
Resignation letter?

05:38.539 --> 05:41.606
I assumed you'd need
some sort of documentation.

05:41.642 --> 05:43.375
[laughing]
This a joke?

05:43.410 --> 05:44.743
No.

05:47.114 --> 05:49.247
I don't know what
to say.

05:49.350 --> 05:50.816
I'm sorry.
You know how difficult

05:50.851 --> 05:52.851
this has been. I --
-I take that back.

05:52.953 --> 05:54.219
I know what to say.

05:54.254 --> 05:56.288
What are you doing
with those files?

05:56.323 --> 05:57.789
These are my research.

05:57.825 --> 05:59.024
But you don't own
your research

05:59.126 --> 06:00.826
while you work
for Project Blue Book.

06:00.894 --> 06:02.761
Generals made that clear
from day one.

06:02.830 --> 06:04.196
This whole science
of UFOlogy, the --

06:04.264 --> 06:06.531
the classification system?
I created that.

06:06.567 --> 06:07.833
I am entitled to my work.

06:07.868 --> 06:09.468
You're entitled
to get your ass kicked,

06:09.503 --> 06:11.069
if you try to steal
Air Force material

06:11.105 --> 06:12.270
from under my nose again.
-Gentlemen.

06:12.306 --> 06:13.638
I-I'm sorry
to interrupt.

06:13.707 --> 06:15.173
-Not now.
-There's a couple here --

06:15.209 --> 06:16.141
[ Suspenseful music plays ]
Not now, Faye!

06:16.176 --> 06:18.009
Sir, I asked you
to wait outside.

06:18.112 --> 06:19.311
I understand,
but we can't.

06:19.413 --> 06:20.645
My husband
needs your help.

06:20.681 --> 06:22.180
Who are you?
How'd you get on this base?

06:22.216 --> 06:25.016
I have
military ID, sir.

06:25.085 --> 06:28.186
I'm Thomas and this is
my wife, Vivian.

06:28.222 --> 06:30.088
Well, Thomas,
I'm sorry, but,

06:30.124 --> 06:32.691
we don't see people
who don't have appointments.

06:32.726 --> 06:35.060
I already tried
that, sir.

06:35.129 --> 06:35.894
We're not leavin'.

06:35.929 --> 06:39.197
♪

06:39.233 --> 06:40.732
Faye, can you get
a couple MPs

06:40.834 --> 06:41.900
to escort these two
off of the --

06:41.935 --> 06:43.402
We are not leavin'.

06:43.437 --> 06:44.736
Thomas, no.

06:44.772 --> 06:45.971
-It's okay, baby.
-What's happenin' here?

06:46.006 --> 06:47.472
We traveled a long way

06:47.508 --> 06:49.207
and we have nowhere
left to turn.

06:49.243 --> 06:50.475
I need your help --

06:50.577 --> 06:53.445
[ Groaning ]

06:53.480 --> 06:54.579
Don't!

06:54.615 --> 06:58.183
♪

06:58.218 --> 07:00.886
Do you need a doctor?

07:00.921 --> 07:02.988
I've been
to the doctors.

07:03.056 --> 07:05.524
But they can't help
because they don't

07:05.559 --> 07:08.326
understand
who did this to me.

07:08.429 --> 07:11.129
Did what to you?

07:11.165 --> 07:13.732
Abducted me.

07:13.767 --> 07:15.634
The aliens
who abducted me.

07:15.702 --> 07:19.638
[ Suspenseful music climbs ]

07:19.673 --> 07:20.972
[ Suspenseful
chord strikes ]

07:23.428 --> 07:25.795
We have no choice now.
Go.

07:25.864 --> 07:28.264
You're wrong, you know.
You do have a choice.

07:28.300 --> 07:29.733
Put the gun down,
no one gets hurt.

07:29.768 --> 07:30.967
We can work out
whatever you need.

07:31.036 --> 07:32.402
Oh, you think
I'd believe that,

07:32.504 --> 07:33.470
comin' from you?

07:33.505 --> 07:36.039
[ Rattling ]

07:36.074 --> 07:37.440
You're Captain Quinn,
right?

07:37.542 --> 07:38.808
-We know each other?
-We spoke on the phone

07:38.844 --> 07:42.579
about nine months ago.

07:42.614 --> 07:43.880
The Army man.

07:43.915 --> 07:45.915
Do you remember
what you told me?

07:46.018 --> 07:48.118
Have to say it's slippin'
my mind right now.

07:48.153 --> 07:50.053
You said it sounded
like a wild story.

07:50.088 --> 07:52.322
You'll get back to me.

07:52.357 --> 07:54.858
Now it's only
gotten worse.

07:54.926 --> 07:56.826
This is the one.
-He called Blue Book?

07:56.862 --> 07:58.895
-Before your time.
-Kept callin' once a week

07:58.997 --> 08:01.031
after that.
-What is this all about?

08:01.099 --> 08:03.133
Staff Sergeant Thomas Mann,
here, claims that

08:03.201 --> 08:06.870
aliens kidnapped him
from his car.

08:06.938 --> 08:08.238
I'm Dr. Allen Hynek.
I'm also a member

08:08.273 --> 08:09.572
of Project Blue Book.
-Doc.

08:09.708 --> 08:12.275
I'd like to hear
your story.

08:12.310 --> 08:13.977
That's why you're
here, right,

08:14.046 --> 08:14.878
to tell your story,
so that way,

08:14.913 --> 08:17.313
you can get some help?

08:17.349 --> 08:18.848
None of the doctors
have been able

08:18.917 --> 08:20.850
to tell us
what's wrong.

08:20.886 --> 08:23.720
We didn't know
where else to go.

08:23.822 --> 08:24.754
Would you like
to sit down?

08:24.790 --> 08:26.322
-Doc.
-The man is in pain.

08:26.425 --> 08:27.524
We can't help him,
unless we know

08:27.559 --> 08:29.059
what he's been
through, Captain.

08:29.161 --> 08:32.062
♪

08:32.097 --> 08:33.463
You're right.

08:33.498 --> 08:35.799
A-And I'm sorry.

08:35.834 --> 08:37.100
We've been so busy here.

08:37.135 --> 08:38.835
T-Take a seat.

08:38.904 --> 08:42.305
But everyone has to get
up against that wall.

08:42.340 --> 08:44.841
I'm not puttin'
the gun away.

08:44.910 --> 08:47.110
That's okay.

08:47.179 --> 08:48.912
I'm just gonna
get my pen

08:48.947 --> 08:50.680
and, uh, a booklet,

08:50.715 --> 08:51.848
so that I can take
some notes.

08:51.883 --> 08:57.387
♪

08:57.422 --> 08:58.421
Please, sit down.

08:58.523 --> 09:00.156
[ Wheels scraping floor ]

09:00.192 --> 09:05.929
♪

09:06.031 --> 09:08.098
Just...start
from wherever you like.

09:08.133 --> 09:14.370
♪

09:14.439 --> 09:18.007
Um...

09:18.043 --> 09:20.610
It was last spring.

09:20.645 --> 09:23.513
I was drivin' back home
after workin' late.

09:23.548 --> 09:24.981
Where's home?

09:25.016 --> 09:26.549
New Hampshire.

09:26.585 --> 09:29.819
♪

09:29.888 --> 09:33.756
There was no moon that night,
just a sky full of stars.

09:33.792 --> 09:34.757
[ Crickets chirping ]

09:34.793 --> 09:38.461
[<i> Radio plays R&B</i> ]

09:38.497 --> 09:39.996
[<i> Static crackling</i> ]

09:40.098 --> 09:41.698
Then I see one fallin'

09:41.733 --> 09:45.135
and, mind you, I see shootin'
stars up there all the time.

09:45.170 --> 09:49.272
But, this one, it split apart
into three pieces.

09:49.341 --> 09:51.875
[ Suspenseful music climbs ]

09:51.910 --> 09:57.113
♪

09:57.149 --> 09:58.748
I couldn't believe
my eyes, at first.

09:58.783 --> 10:01.518
♪

10:01.553 --> 10:02.919
So I slammed on my brakes.

10:02.954 --> 10:05.155
[ Tires squealing ]

10:05.257 --> 10:08.458
And these things were
like watchin' me.

10:08.493 --> 10:10.994
[ Eerie music plays ]

10:11.062 --> 10:15.465
I see this other, larger,
craft coming down.

10:15.500 --> 10:19.235
♪

10:19.271 --> 10:20.737
Then this light,

10:20.805 --> 10:23.506
brighter than any sun,
starts comin' down.

10:23.608 --> 10:25.475
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

10:25.510 --> 10:27.877
Thing is,

10:27.913 --> 10:30.980
it didn't hurt my eyes.

10:31.049 --> 10:32.582
I look up.

10:32.651 --> 10:34.617
That's when I start
feeling it.

10:34.653 --> 10:38.922
This -- This energy
passin' through my body

10:39.024 --> 10:41.791
and it's holding me in place.

10:41.826 --> 10:44.594
I'm trying so hard
to move, but I can't.

10:44.696 --> 10:46.596
Then, this

10:46.631 --> 10:52.335
pulling sensation,
like I'm being lifted up!

10:52.370 --> 10:55.972
I'm tryin' to scream, but
[faintly] nothing comes out.

10:56.041 --> 10:59.442
And then

10:59.477 --> 11:00.743
everything goes black.

11:16.661 --> 11:17.727
Thomas.

11:17.762 --> 11:19.028
[ Faye gaps ]

11:19.064 --> 11:20.597
Quinn: Easy, easy.
-[Cries out]

11:20.699 --> 11:22.365
It's okay.
You're safe.

11:22.400 --> 11:23.967
-What happened?
-Remember how,

11:24.002 --> 11:26.035
when you tell the story
sometimes, what happens?

11:28.673 --> 11:30.340
I'm sorry.
I-I'm so s-s--

11:30.442 --> 11:32.775
It's like this
all the time now.

11:32.844 --> 11:35.378
We'll just be talking
and he'll drift off,

11:35.447 --> 11:38.781
start shaking.

11:38.883 --> 11:41.217
One time, I found him
out in the woods,

11:41.286 --> 11:42.819
on the ground,

11:42.854 --> 11:45.188
just mumbling
strange sounds.

11:45.223 --> 11:47.290
♪

11:47.325 --> 11:48.725
Has this been
getting worse?

11:48.760 --> 11:54.163
♪

11:54.199 --> 11:58.368
And you do not recall
what happened next?

11:58.403 --> 12:01.337
All I remember is,
the next morning,

12:01.473 --> 12:04.474
when I woke, I was
still in the car, but,

12:04.542 --> 12:07.543
I was a hundred miles
from where I started.

12:07.612 --> 12:10.446
No idea
how I got there.

12:10.515 --> 12:12.715
Head felt like it
was going to explode.

12:12.784 --> 12:13.750
And you've been
to the doctors.

12:13.785 --> 12:14.884
-Yes, sir.
-All the ones

12:14.919 --> 12:16.085
who've examined him say they

12:16.121 --> 12:17.453
can't find anything wrong.

12:17.522 --> 12:18.721
Ever tried goin'
to a shrink?

12:18.823 --> 12:20.923
I am not crazy!
This really happened!

12:20.959 --> 12:22.825
No one is
calling you a liar.

12:22.861 --> 12:25.094
You're supposed to be
the experts in this.

12:25.130 --> 12:27.130
You don't know what this
has done to him.

12:27.232 --> 12:29.899
He won't eat, won't sleep.

12:30.035 --> 12:31.367
He's not the same man.

12:31.469 --> 12:34.470
♪

12:34.572 --> 12:36.939
I brought something.
Uh,

12:37.008 --> 12:41.611
he keeps drawin' this stuff,
obsessively. Uh.

12:41.713 --> 12:44.280
He'll sometimes sleepwalk
and do these.

12:44.316 --> 12:45.615
Doesn't even remember.

12:45.650 --> 12:47.350
How can you explain that?

12:47.385 --> 12:48.451
It's just --

12:48.486 --> 12:54.957
♪

12:54.993 --> 13:00.129
♪

13:00.198 --> 13:00.997
Did you draw this?

13:01.032 --> 13:04.033
♪

13:04.069 --> 13:06.936
You know what this is?

13:06.971 --> 13:09.105
No.

13:09.140 --> 13:12.041
No, I just keep
seeing it in my head.

13:12.077 --> 13:13.776
Like the others.

13:13.812 --> 13:16.245
What is it?
What do you see?

13:16.281 --> 13:20.383
It's not what I see.
It's what he sees.

13:20.452 --> 13:21.250
It's impossible.

13:21.286 --> 13:30.927
♪

13:31.029 --> 13:33.896
[ Sinister music plays ]

13:33.932 --> 13:43.639
♪

13:43.675 --> 13:47.844
♪

13:47.912 --> 13:49.479
[ Doorbell rings ]

13:49.514 --> 13:51.447
♪

13:51.483 --> 13:54.684
Hey.

13:54.719 --> 13:56.419
Susie.

13:56.488 --> 13:59.188
Can I come in?

13:59.290 --> 14:00.323
[ Gasp ]

14:00.425 --> 14:01.491
[ Dog barking in distance ]

14:01.526 --> 14:08.898
♪

14:09.000 --> 14:10.032
Has he done
this before?

14:10.168 --> 14:12.535
♪

14:12.604 --> 14:14.871
The first time, he said
it was an accident.

14:14.906 --> 14:17.707
Second time, he was drunk.

14:17.776 --> 14:19.008
Strike three,
you're out.

14:19.043 --> 14:22.545
♪

14:22.647 --> 14:24.046
Do you need
a place to stay?

14:24.115 --> 14:25.715
-I can't ask that of you.
-Of course you can.

14:25.750 --> 14:27.316
You have a family.
You're gonna take in

14:27.352 --> 14:29.719
a battered woman? No.
-You're not --

14:29.754 --> 14:32.588
♪

14:32.724 --> 14:35.458
I wanna help.

14:35.493 --> 14:37.193
Just tell me
how can I help.

14:37.228 --> 14:41.197
♪

14:41.299 --> 14:43.399
I don't know how.

14:43.435 --> 14:45.168
I never imagined
this happening to me.

14:45.203 --> 14:49.705
♪

14:49.741 --> 14:51.607
C'mere.

14:51.709 --> 14:52.942
C'mere.

14:52.977 --> 14:54.110
[ Sniffle ]

14:54.145 --> 14:55.411
[ Sniffle ]

14:55.447 --> 14:57.480
♪

14:57.515 --> 14:59.449
[ Sniffle ]

14:59.484 --> 15:01.584
It's okay.

15:01.619 --> 15:05.621
I'm here for
whatever you need.

15:05.657 --> 15:07.390
I can help you
through this.

15:07.425 --> 15:10.293
♪

15:10.361 --> 15:11.427
Is Allen at work?

15:11.463 --> 15:13.696
Yes.

15:13.765 --> 15:15.498
And Joel?

15:15.533 --> 15:18.100
He's at a friend's.

15:18.136 --> 15:21.103
Good.

15:21.139 --> 15:22.405
Because you know
what would help me

15:22.440 --> 15:23.339
through this right now?

15:23.374 --> 15:26.409
♪

15:26.444 --> 15:27.877
You and I getting
very drunk.

15:27.912 --> 15:32.014
♪

15:32.116 --> 15:33.516
[ Laughs ]

15:33.551 --> 15:34.684
[ Laughter ]

15:34.719 --> 15:36.786
♪

15:36.821 --> 15:39.455
Those all the places people
reported seeing spaceships?

15:39.591 --> 15:40.656
Yes.

15:40.692 --> 15:50.233
♪

15:50.268 --> 15:53.970
♪

15:54.005 --> 15:54.904
[whispering] Something
I need to tell you

15:55.006 --> 15:56.939
about our friend
Thomas.

15:56.975 --> 15:59.041
Reason I never called him
in for an interview.

15:59.077 --> 16:00.409
Did a background
check on 'im,

16:00.512 --> 16:01.978
since he was military.
Turns out he got

16:02.013 --> 16:04.046
shell shock after
fighting overseas.

16:04.082 --> 16:06.215
Got discharged,
Section 8.

16:06.251 --> 16:08.718
Faye, do you have a compact
on you, by any chance?

16:08.753 --> 16:09.719
I do.

16:09.754 --> 16:10.853
May I see it, please?

16:10.889 --> 16:12.455
Did you not hear
what I just said?

16:12.524 --> 16:14.557
Guy's got
a screw loose.

16:14.626 --> 16:17.126
Just...stand behind me,
this side.

16:17.195 --> 16:18.694
Hold this over my shoulder,
so I can see it.

16:18.730 --> 16:20.596
-Why?
-Just do it, please.

16:20.632 --> 16:28.371
♪

16:28.406 --> 16:30.840
Impossible.

16:30.875 --> 16:32.108
Stand here.
Do what I've just done.

16:32.143 --> 16:39.882
♪

16:39.951 --> 16:40.883
They're the same.

16:40.919 --> 16:47.723
♪

16:47.759 --> 16:51.861
So, this is a view
of the star cluster Pleiades,

16:51.963 --> 16:54.697
the Seven Sisters,
as seen from Earth,

16:54.732 --> 16:57.500
444 light-years away.

16:57.535 --> 16:59.502
This is your drawing,
Thomas,

16:59.604 --> 17:02.605
a mirror image
of that same cluster,

17:02.674 --> 17:04.240
which means
that your perspective

17:04.309 --> 17:07.176
is looking back at it
from a position in space

17:07.211 --> 17:08.344
no one has ever been.

17:08.379 --> 17:10.546
♪

17:10.615 --> 17:11.914
S-So what
does that mean?

17:11.950 --> 17:15.284
Well, either he drew
a random set of dots

17:15.320 --> 17:17.286
which align exactly

17:17.322 --> 17:20.289
with a map most people
have never seen,

17:20.325 --> 17:25.661
a one in a hundred
billion chance, or...

17:25.730 --> 17:28.831
someone in that spaceship
taught you how to do it.

17:28.967 --> 17:31.500
♪

17:31.536 --> 17:36.272
[ Suspenseful music climbs ]

17:39.603 --> 17:46.408
♪

17:46.443 --> 17:50.813
♪

17:50.848 --> 17:53.048
This is gonna go
down so fast.

17:53.117 --> 17:56.518
Well, there is plenty
more where that came from.

17:56.554 --> 17:57.586
[ Clink ]
[ Breathy chuckle ]

17:57.621 --> 18:01.023
♪

18:01.058 --> 18:02.691
You are a lifesaver.

18:02.726 --> 18:07.129
You know that?

18:07.198 --> 18:10.265
I just --
I felt so bad that I --

18:10.301 --> 18:12.334
♪

18:12.436 --> 18:14.169
I never suspected
anything before.

18:14.205 --> 18:16.238
Why would you?
You, of all people, know

18:16.307 --> 18:17.372
that we don't show the world

18:17.474 --> 18:19.208
what goes on
behind closed doors.

18:19.243 --> 18:21.476
With all the secrets Allen's
been keeping these days.

18:21.512 --> 18:28.083
♪

18:28.118 --> 18:30.986
What is it?

18:31.021 --> 18:32.054
It's nothing.

18:32.089 --> 18:33.322
We are fine.

18:33.357 --> 18:34.590
No, no, no.
You do not get

18:34.625 --> 18:36.525
to keep secrets
from me now.

18:36.627 --> 18:37.860
We're past all that,
don't you think?

18:37.895 --> 18:40.562
♪

18:40.664 --> 18:41.797
Allen's quitting
Blue Book.

18:41.832 --> 18:44.466
I'm making him.

18:44.501 --> 18:46.368
Why?

18:46.403 --> 18:49.004
I mean, there have been
some crazy things

18:49.106 --> 18:50.839
that have happened since
he started working there.

18:50.875 --> 18:52.341
Like me buying a gun?

18:52.376 --> 18:53.275
[ Scoff ]

18:53.310 --> 18:55.711
♪

18:55.746 --> 18:58.013
I never told him
about it.

18:58.048 --> 19:01.016
That was
the final straw:

19:01.085 --> 19:03.151
every day, feeling like
there were

19:03.220 --> 19:05.954
so many things we were
hiding from each other.

19:05.990 --> 19:07.055
[ Dog barking in distance ]

19:07.091 --> 19:09.825
♪

19:09.860 --> 19:12.127
God, why are we
talking about me?

19:12.162 --> 19:14.997
My problems
must seem so...

19:15.065 --> 19:16.498
trivial right now.

19:16.533 --> 19:20.903
Not at all, because we
have the same ones.

19:20.938 --> 19:22.504
The men in our lives.

19:22.539 --> 19:23.805
[ Laughter ]

19:23.841 --> 19:25.107
[ Clink ]

19:27.411 --> 19:28.510
[ Rattle-thud ]

19:28.545 --> 19:29.444
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

19:29.480 --> 19:31.346
[ Knocking ]

19:31.482 --> 19:33.882
[ Rattling ]

19:33.918 --> 19:34.983
It's not normal
for that door

19:35.019 --> 19:36.285
[ Knocking ]
to be locked.

19:36.320 --> 19:37.920
He'll come back,
or someone else will,

19:37.955 --> 19:39.154
probably with keys.

19:39.256 --> 19:40.389
-What about the map?
-What about it?

19:40.424 --> 19:41.857
Doesn't that
change things?

19:41.892 --> 19:43.725
You said there's no way
it could be random,

19:43.794 --> 19:45.160
that someone
or<i> something</i>

19:45.229 --> 19:46.695
had to have shown him
how to draw that.

19:46.730 --> 19:47.863
Doesn't that prove
what we've been saying?

19:47.898 --> 19:49.798
You know
what pareidolia is?

19:49.833 --> 19:52.000
It's a term used for when
you see recognizable shapes

19:52.069 --> 19:54.603
in random patterns,
like faces in the clouds.

19:54.672 --> 19:56.672
Or dots that look like
star patterns. That is

19:56.707 --> 19:58.540
what it's called, right, Doc?
-Yeah, that is the term, yes.

19:58.575 --> 20:00.742
-Thomas, the longer
you continue this stunt,

20:00.811 --> 20:02.577
the greater the chances are
of someone getting hurt.

20:02.613 --> 20:04.212
Because someone will come
in there, eventually,

20:04.248 --> 20:06.581
and, if you make
one more mistake --

20:06.650 --> 20:08.383
You believe him,
right?

20:08.485 --> 20:10.152
There's still a lot
which doesn't connect, yet,

20:10.220 --> 20:11.320
and the lack of any
physical evidence --

20:11.388 --> 20:12.821
What about the pain
in my head?

20:12.856 --> 20:14.256
That's physical.
-The pain in your head

20:14.325 --> 20:15.991
could be from shell shock,
Thomas.

20:16.093 --> 20:17.492
-Ugh!
-Hynek: I know about
your record, too.

20:17.528 --> 20:19.962
Exposure to trauma in war
can affect us in many ways

20:19.997 --> 20:21.129
and you never
sought treatment.

20:21.165 --> 20:22.864
This has nothing to do
with the war!

20:22.900 --> 20:25.100
I dealt with my fair share
when I came home, too.

20:25.202 --> 20:26.568
Some guys never get over it.
-This is not about the war!

20:26.603 --> 20:28.036
Here's what I think
happened.

20:28.105 --> 20:29.471
You were driving home
that night. Something

20:29.573 --> 20:30.839
triggered a memory
of the battlefield.

20:30.874 --> 20:32.641
-No!
-You passed out
behind the wheel.

20:32.676 --> 20:35.544
No, the spaceship
was real!

20:35.579 --> 20:37.079
You're the one
that's full of shit!

20:37.114 --> 20:38.380
[scoff] How am I the one
that's full of shit,

20:38.482 --> 20:39.548
when you don't even
remember what happened?!

20:39.650 --> 20:41.350
What if I can help him
recall it?

20:41.418 --> 20:42.651
Hypnosis.

20:42.720 --> 20:44.186
Under a trance state,
we can access memories

20:44.221 --> 20:45.787
which have become repressed
or unavailable

20:45.823 --> 20:48.123
to the conscious mind,
traumatic experiences.

20:48.225 --> 20:49.758
Thomas, you let me
put you under,

20:49.860 --> 20:51.893
I'll be able to find out
what happened,

20:51.929 --> 20:54.429
even if that is
shell shock.

20:54.465 --> 20:56.131
I can find that out, too.

20:56.166 --> 20:57.532
You know how
to do that?

20:57.634 --> 20:59.368
A colleague taught me how
for a thesis, yes.

20:59.403 --> 21:00.535
All right.

21:00.571 --> 21:03.071
♪

21:03.173 --> 21:05.273
You put me to sleep,

21:05.309 --> 21:07.009
you could find out
the truth?

21:07.044 --> 21:09.511
Yes.

21:09.546 --> 21:11.013
[ Clink ]
[ Laughter ]

21:11.115 --> 21:14.049
I am feeling so much
better right now.

21:14.084 --> 21:15.817
Oh, good. Because I am
not feeling anything.

21:15.853 --> 21:18.253
[ Laughter ]
[<i> Radio plays blues</i> ]

21:18.288 --> 21:21.123
You always know how
to make me feel better.

21:21.158 --> 21:25.660
♪

21:25.696 --> 21:27.129
I need to use
the little girls' room.

21:27.164 --> 21:28.764
♪

21:28.799 --> 21:30.799
I will get you some water,
in the meantime.

21:30.934 --> 21:32.034
Good idea.

21:32.069 --> 21:36.104
♪

21:36.140 --> 21:37.305
Oh.
[ Laughter ]

21:37.374 --> 21:38.974
-Careful, now.
-Sorry.

21:39.009 --> 21:44.713
♪

21:44.748 --> 21:47.549
[ Sinister music plays ]

21:47.584 --> 21:52.654
♪

21:52.689 --> 21:56.324
[ Tap running ]

21:56.427 --> 21:57.292
[ Faucet squeaks ]

21:57.327 --> 22:02.998
♪

22:03.067 --> 22:06.068
[ Suspenseful music climbs ]

22:06.103 --> 22:10.372
♪

22:10.407 --> 22:12.707
[ Footsteps approaching ]

22:12.810 --> 22:14.176
[chuckling ] I think
I drank too much.

22:14.211 --> 22:15.310
Here, down this.

22:15.412 --> 22:16.511
It'll make you feel better.

22:16.547 --> 22:18.246
♪

22:18.315 --> 22:19.681
My turn to use the bathroom.

22:19.750 --> 22:20.649
[ Dog barks in distance ]

22:20.751 --> 22:21.650
[ Sniff]

22:21.685 --> 22:28.757
♪

22:28.826 --> 22:31.426
This is Dr. Allen Hynek
and I'm here with

22:31.462 --> 22:33.562
Thomas Mann
and I am going to attempt

22:33.597 --> 22:35.430
to place him
in a hypnotic state,

22:35.499 --> 22:38.233
in order to access
memories of his alleged

22:38.268 --> 22:42.104
encounter with
an alien spacecraft.

22:42.172 --> 22:43.271
Thomas, if you could

22:43.307 --> 22:46.108
ac-ac-acknowledge
yourself, please.

22:46.210 --> 22:48.009
This is Thomas.

22:48.045 --> 22:49.044
I'm here.

22:49.146 --> 22:50.545
Okay. Now,

22:50.614 --> 22:53.381
I want you to focus
on this light.

22:53.417 --> 22:57.853
Just relax and focus
on the bulb itself.

22:57.921 --> 22:59.621
Breathing easy,

22:59.723 --> 23:02.724
[muffled] fix your gaze
upon it, and just relax.

23:02.759 --> 23:04.392
Safety's on, right?

23:04.428 --> 23:07.729
Just so nothing goes
off accidentally.

23:07.831 --> 23:09.764
I grew up in New Hampshire.

23:09.800 --> 23:10.832
My husband was
in the military.

23:10.901 --> 23:12.501
I know how
to handle a gun.

23:12.536 --> 23:13.935
[scoffing] Well, this is
a whole different kinda

23:13.971 --> 23:17.339
situation, though,
isn't it? You do realize

23:17.407 --> 23:18.673
the kind of trouble you're
in right now, right?

23:18.709 --> 23:20.909
If this helps Thomas,
it'll be worth it.

23:20.944 --> 23:22.110
What if it doesn't?

23:22.146 --> 23:24.012
-Then we'll keep trying.
-From prison?

23:24.047 --> 23:25.714
-Why don't you believe him?
-I think I explained myself

23:25.816 --> 23:26.781
pretty clearly earlier.

23:26.817 --> 23:28.350
A man comes to you in pain,

23:28.385 --> 23:31.153
asks for help,
and you don't even try?

23:31.188 --> 23:32.320
What is wrong with you?

23:32.356 --> 23:33.922
I'm not the one
holding hostages.

23:33.957 --> 23:35.090
Maybe we wouldn't have to,
if you would've just

23:35.125 --> 23:37.025
listened
to what he had to say!

23:37.060 --> 23:38.460
[ Grumbles ]

23:38.495 --> 23:41.563
I've known him
nearly fifteen years.

23:41.598 --> 23:43.265
I love him.

23:43.367 --> 23:45.267
I trust him.

23:45.302 --> 23:46.768
And, if he says aliens
abducted him,

23:46.803 --> 23:48.904
then I believe him.

23:48.939 --> 23:52.407
And I'll do whatever I can
to help him get better.

23:52.442 --> 23:54.943
Do you not have anyone in your
life you'd do that for?

23:59.983 --> 24:01.516
No wonder
you don't understand.

24:04.955 --> 24:06.788
-[Breathing deeply]
-Hynek: Excellent, Thomas.

24:06.890 --> 24:08.390
Now, as if it were
the easiest thing

24:08.425 --> 24:10.825
in the world,
I want you to just

24:10.961 --> 24:12.627
drift away...

24:12.763 --> 24:14.629
[ Exhales ]

24:14.665 --> 24:17.832
...drifting back

24:17.935 --> 24:19.801
to the moment you
encountered the craft.

24:19.836 --> 24:22.470
♪

24:22.506 --> 24:23.672
[ Gasp ]

24:23.774 --> 24:25.640
♪

24:25.742 --> 24:28.610
I'm not in the car anymore.

24:28.645 --> 24:32.113
I'm inside the ship.

24:32.182 --> 24:33.181
I can't move.

24:33.217 --> 24:37.018
♪

24:37.054 --> 24:39.087
Wait.

24:39.189 --> 24:42.290
[ Warbling ]

24:42.326 --> 24:44.793
Now there's someone here.

24:44.828 --> 24:47.529
I can't quite
make him out.

24:47.631 --> 24:48.697
He's coming toward me.

24:48.732 --> 24:52.400
♪

24:52.502 --> 24:57.672
I'm hearing words
inside my head like...

24:57.708 --> 25:01.509
they were my own thoughts.

25:01.545 --> 25:03.511
But they're not.

25:03.547 --> 25:05.313
They're his.

25:05.349 --> 25:09.184
♪

25:09.219 --> 25:12.554
"Relax.

25:12.656 --> 25:14.856
We only want to understand.

25:14.891 --> 25:16.124
[ Resonating tune ]

25:16.226 --> 25:18.793
These tests
will help us discover

25:18.829 --> 25:22.030
the differences between us."

25:22.065 --> 25:24.165
[ Echoing clang ]

25:24.201 --> 25:27.002
What is that?

25:27.070 --> 25:28.370
I don't like that.

25:28.405 --> 25:30.405
♪

25:30.507 --> 25:32.741
Ah! Aaaaaaaaah!

25:32.776 --> 25:34.509
It burns!

25:34.544 --> 25:36.478
It bu-u-u-u-u-rns!

25:36.513 --> 25:37.746
My neck, oh!

25:37.781 --> 25:38.780
It bu-u-u-u-u-rns!
-What happened?

25:38.815 --> 25:40.282
What's happening?
-Go!

25:40.384 --> 25:41.616
It's okay, he's just coming
out of the trance!

25:41.652 --> 25:43.218
Oh! Aggh! Oh!

25:43.253 --> 25:45.153
-Where is she?
-Faye?

25:45.255 --> 25:47.522
She just went to the bathroom.
-No! Let me go!

25:47.557 --> 25:48.990
[ Clatter ]
Aah!

25:49.026 --> 25:51.826
The gun, grab it,
there!

25:51.862 --> 25:52.861
[ Gunshot ]

25:52.896 --> 25:54.062
Let her go.

25:54.197 --> 25:56.298
♪

25:56.333 --> 25:57.732
Or he's next.

25:57.768 --> 26:01.436
♪

26:01.471 --> 26:03.104
[ Suspenseful music
intensifies ]

26:03.140 --> 26:04.472
♪

26:04.813 --> 26:06.848
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

26:06.883 --> 26:08.115
All right, you win.

26:08.151 --> 26:10.218
Just put
the gun down.

26:10.320 --> 26:11.686
Go stand over there.

26:11.721 --> 26:12.854
-How dare you.
-Doc.

26:12.889 --> 26:15.423
-I was trying to help you.
-Doc!

26:15.458 --> 26:17.391
[ Cocks gun ]

26:17.427 --> 26:20.428
[ Suspenseful music climbs ]

26:20.463 --> 26:23.764
♪

26:23.800 --> 26:26.200
What happened out here?

26:26.236 --> 26:27.468
The secretary ran out.

26:27.504 --> 26:28.703
You have
about 15 minutes

26:28.771 --> 26:30.505
before this place
is surrounded,

26:30.607 --> 26:32.106
probably with a lot bigger
guns than that one.

26:32.208 --> 26:33.241
I heard you screaming.
I didn't know what to do.

26:33.343 --> 26:35.176
I'm sorry.

26:35.311 --> 26:37.044
Come with me.

26:37.080 --> 26:38.179
Come on.

26:38.214 --> 26:39.747
-Come on!
-Come on. Come on.

26:39.782 --> 26:40.781
Get in there.

26:40.817 --> 26:46.854
♪

26:46.990 --> 26:47.989
[ Groaning ]

26:48.124 --> 26:51.359
♪

26:51.394 --> 26:54.562
Let's get one thing
straight, okay?

26:54.597 --> 26:58.266
You do not
apologize to me.

26:58.334 --> 27:00.735
I'm the one
that's sorry.

27:00.770 --> 27:03.170
It's okay.

27:03.206 --> 27:06.374
We're gonna get
through this.

27:06.409 --> 27:08.109
You are gonna get better.

27:08.244 --> 27:10.311
♪

27:10.346 --> 27:12.280
[ Grunts ]

27:12.315 --> 27:14.081
Quinn:
Look like you're in shock.

27:14.117 --> 27:16.784
-Hey, stop. Stop. Look at me.
-Look, I'm fine, okay?

27:16.819 --> 27:18.953
It's just, I --

27:18.988 --> 27:20.021
Did you hear any
of what he was saying

27:20.056 --> 27:21.122
while we were in here?

27:21.190 --> 27:22.189
When you were
hypnotizing him? No.

27:22.225 --> 27:23.190
Who cares about that?
-I do!

27:23.226 --> 27:24.725
-Why?
-Because I think

27:24.794 --> 27:27.128
he might've been
telling the truth.

27:27.230 --> 27:28.696
I saw them.

27:28.731 --> 27:31.532
For the first time,
the things in that ship.

27:31.601 --> 27:32.900
You did?

27:32.936 --> 27:35.336
Yeah. They, um...

27:35.371 --> 27:37.772
jabbed something
into me,

27:37.807 --> 27:39.240
in my neck.

27:39.275 --> 27:41.609
It must be what's
causing all the pain.

27:41.644 --> 27:43.110
Feel really close.

27:43.146 --> 27:45.279
There's a little lump
under the skin.

27:45.315 --> 27:46.347
I never noticed it before.

27:46.382 --> 27:47.281
Do you feel it?

27:47.317 --> 27:49.517
♪

27:49.586 --> 27:51.686
I do.

27:51.721 --> 27:53.187
I think we have
strong evidence here

27:53.222 --> 27:54.956
for a close encounter
of the third kind.

27:54.991 --> 27:56.857
Close encounter
of the first kind:

27:56.893 --> 27:58.859
Visual sighting less
than 500 feet away,

27:58.895 --> 28:01.028
showing angular
extension and detail.

28:01.064 --> 28:03.831
Second kind: an encounter
with a physical effect,

28:03.866 --> 28:05.766
car dying,
lights flickering.

28:05.835 --> 28:07.768
The third...
-Contact. Right, right, right.

28:07.804 --> 28:09.503
the scale you were
workin' on.

28:09.606 --> 28:11.339
Thomas needs a full physical,
under our watch,

28:11.374 --> 28:12.573
Then we're gonna need
to re-interview him.

28:12.675 --> 28:14.742
Also, I wanna see
his car.

28:14.777 --> 28:16.177
Are you forgetting what's
going on here right now?

28:16.212 --> 28:18.279
Of course not! I-I --
He's just scared.

28:18.348 --> 28:19.614
I don't give a damn
what he is.

28:19.649 --> 28:21.182
And you don't even
work here anymore.

28:21.217 --> 28:22.416
♪

28:22.452 --> 28:23.918
Mm.

28:24.053 --> 28:27.355
[ Gasping ]

28:27.457 --> 28:29.957
[ Birds chirping ]

28:29.993 --> 28:31.125
Mimi.

28:31.160 --> 28:33.928
Mm. My head's
spinning.

28:33.963 --> 28:35.696
Maybe you should
lie down.

28:35.732 --> 28:37.732
[ Moans ]

28:37.834 --> 28:39.233
[gasp] I need to.

28:39.268 --> 28:41.135
C'mon.
[ Dog barking in distance ]

28:41.237 --> 28:42.370
Okay.

28:42.405 --> 28:43.504
Okay.
-Oops!

28:43.539 --> 28:45.673
[ Laughter ]

28:45.742 --> 28:47.475
What time is Allen
getting home?

28:47.510 --> 28:48.843
Um,

28:48.878 --> 28:51.345
he has class,
so, late.

28:51.447 --> 28:52.546
Mm.

28:52.582 --> 28:54.281
Let's get you
into the bedroom.

28:54.317 --> 28:57.652
♪

28:57.687 --> 28:59.220
-What are you doing?
-If I don't work here anymore,

28:59.255 --> 29:00.521
then I hypnotized
and recorded Thomas

29:00.556 --> 29:02.223
as a private civilian,
which means

29:02.325 --> 29:03.424
I am entitled
to my interview.

29:03.459 --> 29:05.493
Don't try this again.

29:05.595 --> 29:07.094
You just push me?

29:07.196 --> 29:08.329
I'm not going
to let you take my work!

29:08.364 --> 29:09.697
Do you realize
how many times

29:09.799 --> 29:11.632
that I almost got fired
because of you?

29:11.668 --> 29:13.467
If I didn't lie about what
happened in White Forest...

29:13.503 --> 29:16.237
If you hadn't lied, you'd be
just as bad as all the others!

29:16.305 --> 29:17.972
Pushing the same propaganda,
telling witnesses

29:18.074 --> 29:20.041
what they saw was birds
and weather balloons!

29:20.076 --> 29:21.542
How much evidence
do you need?!

29:21.577 --> 29:24.779
♪

29:24.881 --> 29:26.113
What are you lookin' for?

29:26.182 --> 29:27.615
If Captain Quinn is right
and we're about to be

29:27.650 --> 29:29.083
surrounded, we have
to do this now.

29:29.118 --> 29:31.385
♪

29:31.421 --> 29:32.987
Cut this thing
outta my neck.

29:33.022 --> 29:36.624
♪

29:36.759 --> 29:38.092
[ Grunting ]

29:38.194 --> 29:40.294
No. I'm not gonna cut you
open, Thomas.

29:40.329 --> 29:41.862
Baby, no one
is gonna believe me,

29:41.931 --> 29:43.431
unless we have
the physical proof!

29:43.566 --> 29:46.133
[ Grunting ]

29:46.169 --> 29:49.370
♪

29:49.405 --> 29:51.972
Listen, this might be
our only chance.

29:52.008 --> 29:53.074
They're comin'!

29:53.109 --> 29:55.509
[ Muffled shouting ]

29:55.545 --> 29:57.445
[ Suspenseful music climbs ]

29:57.480 --> 29:58.379
[ Moans ]

29:58.481 --> 30:03.818
♪

30:03.853 --> 30:05.419
[ Moaning ]

30:05.455 --> 30:07.121
Let's take off your shoes.

30:07.256 --> 30:10.091
♪

30:10.126 --> 30:12.193
[ Eerie music plays ]

30:12.228 --> 30:13.194
[ Clattering ]

30:13.229 --> 30:14.395
[ Thud ]
Ah!

30:14.430 --> 30:18.165
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

30:18.301 --> 30:21.335
[ Grunting next door ]

30:21.370 --> 30:23.137
♪

30:23.172 --> 30:24.839
-What?
-Shh.

30:24.874 --> 30:26.807
♪

30:26.843 --> 30:28.175
Hm.

30:28.211 --> 30:31.011
[ Suspenseful music climbs ]

30:31.047 --> 30:34.582
♪

30:34.684 --> 30:35.783
[ Thud ]

30:35.818 --> 30:37.384
-[Squelching]
-[Grunting next door]

30:37.420 --> 30:38.719
[ Groaning ]

30:38.755 --> 30:41.288
[ Grunting continues ]

30:41.324 --> 30:43.190
[ Footsteps shuffling ]

30:43.226 --> 30:48.462
[ Grunting continues ]

30:48.498 --> 30:49.897
[ Thud ]

30:49.932 --> 30:58.939
♪

30:58.975 --> 31:00.374
♪

31:00.476 --> 31:02.343
[ Sinister sting plays ]

31:02.445 --> 31:04.779
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

31:04.814 --> 31:12.553
♪

31:12.588 --> 31:16.657
♪

31:16.692 --> 31:18.893
[ Grunts ]

31:18.928 --> 31:21.228
[ Panting ]

31:21.264 --> 31:22.296
Are we done?

31:22.331 --> 31:25.699
♪

31:25.802 --> 31:29.003
Listen.

31:29.038 --> 31:30.271
I don't hear anything.

31:30.339 --> 31:31.438
Exactly.

31:31.474 --> 31:33.007
[ Chair creaking ]

31:33.042 --> 31:37.411
♪

31:37.446 --> 31:39.847
[ Gasping ]

31:39.882 --> 31:43.717
♪

31:43.786 --> 31:44.752
[shakily]
I got it out.

31:44.787 --> 31:47.354
♪

31:47.390 --> 31:49.590
Whatever those creatures
put in him...

31:49.659 --> 31:50.758
[ Suspenseful music climbs ]

31:50.793 --> 31:51.692
...I got it out.

31:51.727 --> 31:57.231
♪

31:58.866 --> 32:01.200
I can't be sure what kind.

32:01.269 --> 32:03.536
Feels almost hollow, though.

32:03.571 --> 32:04.937
You ever take
any ordinance overseas?

32:04.973 --> 32:06.739
I was wounded, yes.

32:06.774 --> 32:07.873
In the shoulder.

32:07.909 --> 32:09.208
Can I have a look?

32:15.683 --> 32:18.184
Could be shrapnel.

32:18.286 --> 32:19.685
That's
perfectly round.

32:19.721 --> 32:21.354
I've seen metal pulled
out of people's bodies

32:21.389 --> 32:23.422
you'd swear looked
like Abe Lincoln.

32:23.524 --> 32:24.790
Anything's possible.

32:29.030 --> 32:29.962
[ Zap ]

32:29.998 --> 32:31.564
-What happened?
-Nothing.

32:31.633 --> 32:33.266
That could've just been
a reflection off the, uh --

32:33.301 --> 32:35.334
[ Electricity buzzing ]

32:35.370 --> 32:37.703
Is that...
what's doing that?

32:37.805 --> 32:38.738
[ Clang ]

32:38.773 --> 32:40.640
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

32:40.708 --> 32:41.741
It's...that thing.

32:41.843 --> 32:42.608
It killed the power.

32:42.644 --> 32:43.943
No.

32:43.978 --> 32:45.011
And my phone is gonna...

32:45.079 --> 32:46.445
[ Ring ]

32:46.514 --> 32:47.513
...any moment.

32:47.548 --> 32:48.547
What's happening?

32:48.650 --> 32:50.116
My guess?

32:50.151 --> 32:52.118
[ Ring ]
MPs have surrounded the place

32:52.186 --> 32:53.886
and are cutting the power.

32:53.921 --> 32:54.720
The person on the other
end of that phone

32:54.789 --> 32:56.188
is a commander,
[ Ring ]

32:56.291 --> 32:58.524
looking to make contact,
start a dialogue.

32:58.559 --> 33:00.459
Whatever happens next,
how peacefully

33:00.495 --> 33:01.427
[ Ring ]
you wanna resolve this,

33:01.462 --> 33:05.464
is up to you.
So, Thomas,

33:05.533 --> 33:07.867
[ Ring ]
how would you like
to proceed?

33:07.969 --> 33:10.236
♪

33:10.271 --> 33:11.504
[ Ring ]

33:11.539 --> 33:14.073
[<i> Ring</i> ]

33:14.108 --> 33:17.743
[<i> Ring</i> ]

33:17.879 --> 33:20.780
[<i> Ring</i> ]

33:20.815 --> 33:23.716
[ Speaking Russian ]

33:43.971 --> 33:46.205
[ Ring ]

33:46.274 --> 33:47.506
You should answer.

33:47.575 --> 33:49.141
-What do they want?
-They just wanna talk,

33:49.177 --> 33:50.576
[ Ring ]
find out what's going on.

33:50.611 --> 33:52.078
-You can show them
that thing now, right,

33:52.113 --> 33:53.946
that was in my neck?

33:54.048 --> 33:55.448
[ Ring ]

33:55.483 --> 33:57.350
You believe us now,
don't you?

33:57.452 --> 33:58.751
That's what was
making me crazy,

33:58.786 --> 34:00.019
what caused all this.
[ Ring ]

34:00.054 --> 34:01.754
Foreign objects can
affect body chemistry,

34:01.823 --> 34:03.622
regardless of what they are.
He has a point.

34:03.658 --> 34:04.724
This is
outta my hands now.

34:04.759 --> 34:06.025
[ Ring ]
What can we do?

34:06.060 --> 34:08.327
Put the gun down.
We'll go from there.

34:08.363 --> 34:10.930
Babe.
[ Ring ]

34:10.965 --> 34:12.832
You said something earlier
about me getting help.

34:12.900 --> 34:15.067
-Yeah.
-What if this is a reaction

34:15.169 --> 34:16.268
to what I saw overseas?

34:16.304 --> 34:17.436
Maybe I haven't been
in my right mind.

34:17.472 --> 34:18.838
-Thomas.
-Maybe I did make it all up.

34:18.873 --> 34:19.939
You don't mean that!
[ Ring ]

34:20.041 --> 34:21.340
Thomas, the hypnosis
does raise

34:21.376 --> 34:22.942
some interesting questions.
-If I'm the one

34:22.977 --> 34:24.777
who caused all this,
[ Ring ]

34:24.912 --> 34:27.713
Vivian shouldn't go
to jail.

34:27.782 --> 34:29.615
None of this is her fault.
I don't want her to get

34:29.650 --> 34:30.816
[ Ring ]
in trouble for what I did.

34:30.918 --> 34:32.685
Stop saying that!

34:32.720 --> 34:34.620
You didn't make this up.
You just needed help.

34:34.655 --> 34:35.688
[ Ring ]
You can see that now, right?

34:35.723 --> 34:36.756
Baby, please.

34:36.791 --> 34:39.692
You didn't do
anything wrong.

34:39.727 --> 34:41.327
Why should you have
to suffer for that?

34:41.462 --> 34:45.231
♪

34:45.333 --> 34:48.000
Why did the phone
stop ringing?

34:48.069 --> 34:49.068
I don't know.

34:49.103 --> 34:51.303
♪

34:51.339 --> 34:52.671
-Thomas.
-Vivian: Can you call back?

34:52.707 --> 34:54.106
Get away from the window!
-Thomas!

34:54.142 --> 34:56.108
[ Gunshot ]
Aah! Thomas! Thomas!

34:56.210 --> 34:57.143
Thomas!
-Ah!

34:57.178 --> 34:58.310
-Thomas!
-Go! Go! Go!

34:58.346 --> 34:59.512
Hey, let me see your hands!
-Thomas!

34:59.647 --> 35:00.679
-Keep 'em in the air!
-Thomas!

35:00.715 --> 35:02.882
[sobbing] No! No! No!

35:02.917 --> 35:03.983
[ Suspenseful music climbs ]
MP: Window, window, yeah!

35:04.018 --> 35:05.017
Vivian: No!

35:05.153 --> 35:09.555
♪

35:12.647 --> 35:13.613
Hold it, ma'am.

35:13.648 --> 35:14.814
Oh, it's all right.

35:14.849 --> 35:16.182
She should go
with her husband.

35:16.217 --> 35:18.784
Yes, sir.

35:18.820 --> 35:21.187
Bullet passed
right through.

35:21.289 --> 35:23.322
I've seen that before.
He should be all right.

35:23.391 --> 35:25.958
Can't say for sure
what'll happen after that.

35:25.994 --> 35:28.227
I understand.

35:28.263 --> 35:30.963
And I'm sorry.

35:30.999 --> 35:35.034
You saved my life
at the window.

35:35.069 --> 35:37.670
Couple inches to the right
and that bullet hits my head.

35:37.705 --> 35:39.739
I'm just sorry things
had to go that far.

35:39.774 --> 35:42.642
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

35:42.677 --> 35:44.610
♪

35:44.646 --> 35:46.679
I just want an answer.

35:46.748 --> 35:48.180
So do I.

35:48.216 --> 35:56.255
♪

35:56.291 --> 36:05.998
♪

36:06.034 --> 36:15.741
♪

36:15.777 --> 36:25.484
♪

36:25.520 --> 36:35.227
♪

36:35.263 --> 36:44.971
♪

36:45.006 --> 36:47.239
♪

36:47.275 --> 36:48.975
You're not gonna walk
off with that.

36:49.043 --> 36:50.643
What do<i> you</i> wanna do
with it?

36:50.678 --> 36:52.278
Put it with the tape,

36:52.313 --> 36:53.846
deal with it
when I get back.

36:59.120 --> 37:00.286
[ Rattling ]

37:01.389 --> 37:02.388
[ Breathy chuckle ]

37:04.025 --> 37:06.525
I gotta go outta town,
D.C.

37:06.594 --> 37:08.661
Generals have some
conference there

37:08.696 --> 37:10.129
they'd like me
to attend.

37:10.164 --> 37:13.199
You know you have
a cut above your, uh --

37:13.267 --> 37:14.867
I believe that came
from you, earlier.

37:17.205 --> 37:19.605
You've gotten better since
that bar fight in Alabama.

37:23.478 --> 37:24.977
Ahem.

37:25.013 --> 37:28.781
You never signed this,
by the way.

37:28.850 --> 37:30.583
You'll have to, if you
wanna make it official.

37:30.618 --> 37:34.687
[ Melancholy tune plays ]

37:34.722 --> 37:37.857
I'd like you
to reconsider.

37:37.925 --> 37:39.392
I think, if it was you
who answered the phone

37:39.427 --> 37:40.660
when Thomas called
that day,

37:40.695 --> 37:43.429
none of this
would have happened.

37:43.464 --> 37:48.467
You're good at that:
keeping me honest.

37:48.503 --> 37:51.704
I think, uh,

37:51.739 --> 37:53.139
I think I'm better
when you're around.

37:53.174 --> 37:55.374
♪

37:55.476 --> 37:57.009
But I understand
if you wanna leave.

37:57.045 --> 38:01.080
♪

38:01.149 --> 38:03.249
Do you believe in any
of what Thomas said?

38:03.284 --> 38:06.285
[ Sigh ]

38:06.320 --> 38:08.387
Doesn't matter
what I believe.

38:08.423 --> 38:09.555
That's not why
we're here.

38:09.590 --> 38:13.059
♪

38:13.161 --> 38:14.427
No need to lock up.

38:14.462 --> 38:19.732
♪

38:19.801 --> 38:22.468
[ Exhales slowly ]

38:22.570 --> 38:23.502
[ Door opens, closes ]

38:23.538 --> 38:25.938
♪

38:25.973 --> 38:30.543
[ on radio ]
♪<i> If you love me</i> ♪

38:30.578 --> 38:32.378
[ Door opens ]

38:32.480 --> 38:35.147
♪<i> Oh, Donna</i> ♪

38:35.216 --> 38:36.315
♪<i> Oh, Donna</i> ♪

38:36.350 --> 38:37.650
You were quick today.

38:37.685 --> 38:39.585
You know me,
once I make up my mind.

38:39.620 --> 38:43.155
♪

38:43.191 --> 38:44.957
Where is it?

38:44.992 --> 38:47.560
Hmm? The film.

38:47.595 --> 38:50.830
Somewhere safe.

38:50.865 --> 38:52.031
You didn't do it.

38:52.100 --> 38:53.499
Of course I did.
You don't trust me?

38:53.568 --> 38:55.301
You've given me
every reason not to.

38:55.336 --> 39:01.307
♪

39:01.342 --> 39:02.641
How can I change that
for you?

39:02.677 --> 39:08.080
♪

39:08.182 --> 39:09.081
Mnh.

39:09.117 --> 39:16.889
♪

39:16.924 --> 39:24.697
♪

39:24.732 --> 39:26.799
[whispering]
Keep them both there.

39:26.834 --> 39:28.400
[ Shuddering ]

39:28.436 --> 39:32.905
♪

39:32.974 --> 39:33.773
[ Continues
shuddering ]

39:33.808 --> 39:42.414
♪

39:42.450 --> 39:44.517
Now it's self-defense.

39:44.552 --> 39:46.252
[ Three gunshots ]
Ah!

39:46.287 --> 39:48.988
♪

39:49.090 --> 39:50.289
Ahh.

39:50.358 --> 39:52.391
[ Seat creaking ]

39:52.493 --> 39:53.559
[ Gasp ]

39:53.594 --> 39:58.998
♪

39:59.033 --> 40:00.699
[ Lighter clinks ]

40:00.735 --> 40:03.936
♪

40:04.005 --> 40:07.006
♪<i> It's never</i> ♪

40:07.108 --> 40:11.510
♪<i> Too late to make amends</i> ♪

40:11.612 --> 40:14.947
♪<i> I'm gonna love you</i> ♪

40:15.049 --> 40:16.515
♪<i> Until</i> ♪

40:16.551 --> 40:18.450
♪<i> The end</i> ♪

40:18.486 --> 40:22.254
[ Vehicle approaching ]

40:25.760 --> 40:26.492
[ Engine stops,
emergency brake rips ]

40:26.561 --> 40:28.194
[ Door creaks open, slams ]

40:28.229 --> 40:30.296
[ Dog barks in distance ]

40:30.331 --> 40:32.998
[ Crickets chirping ]

40:33.034 --> 40:35.768
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

40:35.803 --> 40:39.038
♪

40:39.073 --> 40:40.606
What are you doing here?

40:40.675 --> 40:42.508
You know where I live?!
-Shh shh shh shh shh.

40:42.543 --> 40:44.376
You're just gonna have
to trust me.

40:44.412 --> 40:45.811
I won't have time
to explain.

40:45.847 --> 40:47.513
No!

40:47.548 --> 40:50.216
You don't come
near my family.

40:50.251 --> 40:52.618
You've already put me
in enough danger.

40:52.687 --> 40:53.919
I have no choice.

40:53.988 --> 40:58.657
[ Suspenseful music
intensifies ]

40:58.693 --> 41:00.459
You need
to leave tonight.

41:00.494 --> 41:04.230
[ Sinister music plays ]

41:04.265 --> 41:05.898
A plane ticket.

41:05.967 --> 41:08.500
Something big is
about to happen,

41:08.569 --> 41:09.602
something you've
been waiting for

41:09.637 --> 41:11.704
since you took
this job.

41:11.739 --> 41:12.771
Proof.

41:12.807 --> 41:16.008
♪

41:16.077 --> 41:17.509
Man:<i> Why not?</i>
-Ginny:<i> I don't want you to.</i>

41:17.545 --> 41:19.245
<i> It might be dangerous.</i>
-There you are.

41:19.313 --> 41:20.746
I was getting worried.
<i> -Only madmen see the saucers,</i>

41:20.781 --> 41:22.681
-Allen, what's wrong?
<i> -but they're dangerous.</i>

41:22.717 --> 41:24.016
<i> There's nothing out</i>
<i> in those hills,</i>
-I need to pack.

41:24.051 --> 41:25.684
<i> but the hills are dangerous.</i>
-Pack for what?

41:25.720 --> 41:26.919
-I have to fly to Washington, DC
<i> -I can't buy that.</i>

41:26.954 --> 41:28.587
-tonight, right now!
<i> -The only way</i>

41:28.623 --> 41:29.889
<i> I can hurt myself is by not</i> --
-What is going on?

41:29.924 --> 41:32.424
[ Click ]
[ Running footsteps ]

41:32.460 --> 41:34.126
-Allen.
<i> -You want breakfast?</i>

41:34.161 --> 41:35.661
-We made a promise, remember?
<i> -Back where?</i>

41:35.696 --> 41:36.996
-No more secrets.
<i> -Stop it. Stop it.</i>

41:37.031 --> 41:38.097
-[Whispering]
<i> -Please stop it.</i>

41:38.132 --> 41:39.632
<i> You can't just [indistinct]</i>

41:39.667 --> 41:41.300
Man:<i> Ginny,</i>
<i> I've gotta find out.</i>

41:41.402 --> 41:42.301
Do you understand?

41:42.336 --> 41:44.536
-Mom?
<i> -Then,</i>

41:44.605 --> 41:45.871
<i> -then I can't stop you.</i>
-Dad,

41:45.940 --> 41:47.306
is everything all right?
-Man:<i> No, you can't.</i>

41:47.408 --> 41:48.607
C'mere.

41:48.709 --> 41:49.675
<i> -But I'll be back, Ginny,</i>

41:49.710 --> 41:50.776
<i> and, so help me, if this</i>

41:50.811 --> 41:52.611
<i> moon shot comes through,</i>
-Joel.

41:52.647 --> 41:53.879
<i> -if John's story is right,</i>
-Your dad needs to go

41:53.915 --> 41:54.880
on a business trip, but,
<i> -it'll mean a new world,</i>

41:54.916 --> 41:56.482
<i> for me, for you,</i>

41:56.517 --> 41:57.950
<i> for the both of us!</i>
-he'll be back soon.

41:57.985 --> 41:59.218
<i> If I can get some proof,</i>
<i> some concrete evidence,</i>

41:59.253 --> 42:00.786
-Right?
<i> -some real documents,</i>

42:00.855 --> 42:02.321
-Yeah, I will.
<i> -that these saucers have been</i>

42:02.356 --> 42:03.722
<i> landing. I know they have.</i>
<i> They've been</i>

42:03.791 --> 42:05.157
<i> landing here for the</i>
<i> last three years,</i>

42:05.259 --> 42:06.625
<i> landing and</i>
<i> discharging passengers.</i>

42:06.694 --> 42:08.560
<i> And where are they?</i>
<i> Here, in Las Palmas,</i>

42:08.663 --> 42:10.062
<i> filtered all over America.</i>

42:10.097 --> 42:11.430
Ginny:<i> You really</i>
<i> believe that, don't you?</i>

42:11.465 --> 42:12.631
Man:<i> I don't know, Ginny,</i>
<i> but I'll find out.</i>

42:12.700 --> 42:13.832
<i> I'll find out a lotta things.</i>

42:13.868 --> 42:15.301
<i> I'll find out why</i>
<i> they come here,</i>

42:15.336 --> 42:16.902
<i> who sent them,</i>
<i> what's behind all this.</i>

42:16.938 --> 42:19.104
